OL,3,CGuernsey residents voice their
OL,4,Csolutions on the island's housing
OL,5,Cshortage
OL,7,FGuernsey's housing crisis is an island-
OL,8,Fwide problem.
OL,10,FIt all comes down to supply and
OL,11,Fdemand, as the small amount of housing
OL,12,Fstock on the island is pushing prices
OL,13,Fup, especially in the rental sector.
OL,15,FOver the past five years, we've seen
OL,16,Fhousing projects delayed, reduced in
OL,17,Fsize, or entirely thrown out, such as
OL,18,Fat Vazon or Leale's Yard.
